<br>
But suddenly my heart began to beat very loud I could feel it in my head (like when u run a lot) but it became so loud I couldnt hear much more than that, at that point I was getting scared. Then suddenly my eyes began to close, I didnt want to and tried to scream but I couldnt, and I couldnt move also. Its so horrible not being able to move, not even my head would move.<br>
<br>
I struggled to keep my eyes open and it suddenly stopped. The next day I thought it was just a dream. But the next 2 days the exact same thing happened at exactly 1:30 am. The second day I wrote everything down on paper right after it happened, so I wouldnt think it was a dream the next day.<br>
<br>
My mother had gave me 3 new pencils the day before, and I was really scared while writing and all 3 pens ran out of inkt right after each other, I got freaked out, They were new!!, I was afraid to get outta bed to grab another but I did, and wrote everything down.<br>
<br>
My grandma died a few days later but I dont think it had anything to do with it, upto today It still happens sometimes, at least twice a week, but not at the same times, only the thought used to scare me, but now I kinda get used to it, and only the actuall moment scares me.<br>
<br>
once I told myself I wouldnt struggle back to see what would happen, I got scared half way and it took a lot of strength to get outta it. I never did it again. I wish I knew what it was, it really scares me at those moments. I didnt drink at those nights, and I'm really sure they werent dreams, besides I wrote it down... I dunno <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ufraterliber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FraterLiber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/6/02 1:20:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=108.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forced to close my eyes</span><hr size=1> You probably woke up, more or less, during sleep paralysis, and it scared the wobblies out of you.<br>
